        <updateDate>2018-05-30T20:06:27Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Perioperative Reduction of Opioids Act or the PRO Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) to convene a technical expert panel to recommend ways to reduce opioid use in surgical settings and best practices for pain management, specifically during the perioperative (pre-operative through post-operative) period. </p> <p>HHS must also report on diagnosis-related group codes that have the highest volume of surgeries and the availability of associated data regarding post-operative opioid use, including prescription patterns and rates of consumption. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
